      <section eId="sec_CCRP-855">
        <num>CCRP 855</num>
        <heading>855. Â Errors discovered after verdict or judgment of guilty; necessary allegations</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-855__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of Article 851 shall contain allegations of fact sworn to by the defendant or his counsel, showing:</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-855__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The specific nature of the error or defect complained of; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-855__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>That, notwithstanding the exercise of reasonable diligence by the defense, the error or defect was not discovered before or during the trial.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112836</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
